<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM3.9.10">
<l>caṅkumali taṇṭumutal cakkaramu ṉēntun tāmaraikkaṇ neṭiyapirāṉ tāṉamaruṅ kōyil</l>
<l>vaṅkamali kaṭalulakil maliveytu nāṅkūr vaikunta viṇṇakarmēl vaṇṭaṟaiyum poḻilcūḻ</l>
<l>maṅkaiyartan talaivaṉmaru valartamuṭal tuṇiya vāḷvīcum parakālaṉ kalikaṉṟi coṉṉa</l>
<l>caṅkamali tamiḻmālai pattivaival lārkaḷ taraṇiyoṭu vicumpāḷun taṉmaipeṟu vārē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master this garland of ten [verses] in Tamil,</l>
<l rend="indent">of which the Caṅkam is proud, composed by Kalikaṉṟi,</l>
<l>Parakālaṉ who swings a sword to sever his enemies’ bodies,</l>
<l rend="indent">leader of those of Maṅkai, girded by gardens where bees hum,</l>
<l>About Vaikunta Viṇṇakaram in Nānkūr which acquires abundance</l>
<l rend="indent">on this earth, [its] seas where waves abound,</l>
<l>The temple where sits the tall lord with lotus eyes, who bears the conch,</l>
<l rend="indent">proud mace, others, and, foremost, the discus,</l>
<l rend="indent">they will gain the qualities which will rule the heavens and the earth.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
